				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hey, all...  Although, I no longer play EQ, I will be investing in a new computer and thought I return to the good ol' boards for some help.  I got an HP pos in '98.  P3 400mhz, ATI RagePro 8mb.  It was always somewhat of a hassle playing EverQuest on it, so I bought a GeForce MMX 400 64mb when that came out, but found the mobo was not compatible.  /rude HP.  So, had to suffer through continued laggy play, never really able to venture deeply into Luclin, LoY, or PoP.  I tried to install WC3 and found it wasn't even good enough for that.  SO, finally after saving some cheese I wanna buy a completely new system.  I don't want to have to buy another one for a long time (I realize "long time" means little in terms of computers).
<br />

<br />
I'd appreciate any help you guys could offer.
<br />

<br />
I have a few basic questions first;
<br />
(Not a big gamer, but I do want the games I may play to play their best - assume money is no object, <span style="font-style: italic"> even if it is</span>)
<br />

<br />
1. AMD or Pentium?
<br />

<br />
2. Is the difference between a P4 2.8ghz processor and a 3.2 terribly noticable assuming both w/ 800mhz fsb and 512mb cache on same mobo?  ie. worth the extra money?
<br />

<br />
3. GeForce or Radeon?  And, is the 5900 256mb Ultra much better than the 5600 128mb Ultra?  I'm not sure what to look for...  Fill rate and memory bandwidth are both more than double the 5600, but really I'm not sure what that means.
<br />

<br />
4. What is RDRam?  Is DDR the best?  What is this new Corsair XMS DDR?  Worth it?  Will 1gb suffice in any case?
<br />

<br />
5. Is "the Alienware difference" really worth the money?  Always had my heart set on one...
<br />

<br />

<br />
ANY other advice/help you can offer would be great, guys.  I hope you're all doing well, and still tearing it up in EQ!  Much love.
<br />

<br />
Stay safe.
<br />
/salute
<br />

<br />
Seth
<br />

<br />
Mystikefini Ali (retired)
<br />
Tunarean Warder</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
