			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Here are my suggestions, and just my suggestions based off personal experience :
<br />

<br />
I'd go AMD. Their CPU's tend to be geared more towards Gamers, and if you're posting on this forum, you are a gamer.
<br />

<br />
My theory when buying a new computer is get something that you can upgrade in the future easily. With an 800 mhz FSB you should be good to just pop in a new chip when you want to for quite a while.
<br />

<br />
Get the best video card you can afford. I'd probably say Radeon is top choice right now. 265 &gt; 128 if you can swing it.
<br />

<br />
Make sure when you buy ram that the mhz (400mhz or whatnot) is running at the speed of the chip. If your chip is running at 333mhz fsb, make sure the ram is running at LEAST 333 mhz or you'll get problems.
<br />

<br />
If I was buying a computer and not building one myself, I would be owning an Alienware. Their machines rock.<br />_________________<br />Peppiwyn Stealtharrow
<br />
55 Ranger on Torvon
<br />
<a href="http://menagerie.homepctech.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">Menagerie</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
