			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">1. AMD is better value for money.  The fastest P4 is faster than the fastest Athlon though.  If money is no object then get the top P4.  If price/performance worries you then get AMD.
<br />
2. The difference between the 2.8 and 3.2 is a little more speed (~15%) for a lot more money.
<br />
3. The GF5900Ultra is the best card on the market at the moment, unless you want to play HL2 which runs a lot faster on Radeon9800s.  256 is better than 128 and more future-proof.  I'd go for 256.
<br />
4. RDRAM is expensive proprietary memory that the P4s used to use before Intel switched to DDR.  They are not compatible.  If you get an RDRAM motherboard you have to use RDRAM.  If you get a DDR motherboard you have to use DDR.  Get DDR.
<br />
5. It means you can mail it back to them if you fook it up.  I rarely buy brand name stuff but their name seems pretty good.
<br />

<br />
Dd</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
