			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">This is the system i bought just this weekend, i did my homework, and it runs well. 
<br />
 
<br />
     P4 2.8 GHz, WITH 800 FBS. importiant your fbs is 800. reason I stuck with 2.8, is because the extra ".4" is not worth over double the price. plus, overclocking can get me to 3.3 no problem.
<br />
  
<br />
     Motherboard is importiant. I stuck with the ASUS P4C800 delux, a bit pricy for a MOBO, but itl last ya. Make sure your board can support at least 2G of ram, DDR ram at that, so that it will be last likely to become out dated.
<br />
  
<br />
     I simply have 1G of kingston 2700 DDR ram. not the best, but money is kind of an issue, and you can hardly tell the difference. Make sure you have 2 sticks of 512, not a 1G stick. This saves money and lets you take advantage of Hyper threading.
<br />

<br />
    The kind of Hard drives I have is 2 Serial ATA 80G. made by Maxtor. SATA hard drives are almost double the cost of traditional hard drives, but the speed is such an advantage. Also i have a RAID 0 setup. For a ocasional gamer, stick with normal. 
<br />

<br />
     My Grafics card is only a ATI 9600 pro. I am partial to Nvidia, but the noticable difference of getting a 5900 ultra would be on games that are not out yet, and once they are, the now high end pixle pushers will be cheaper. plus sticking w/ the ATI saves much money.
<br />
 
<br />
   Nothing special about my optical drives, a simple $15 CD ROM and a $50 Burn drive. I have a DVD player on my TV, if this is also your case, do not waste the money on a DVD player for your computer. Unless you do lots of video editing and you want to burn DVDs. this saves money.
<br />
 
<br />
   My monitor is a simple flat screen E-MACHINE 17inch I bought from Circuit city for $110 (after rebate).  
<br />
   
<br />
    Odds and ends were about $150, mouse, keyboard, system cooler, floppy, cords, NIC. all together this system was about 1k. not to bad. Similar systems sold at CC or BB would be $1500 give or take. not a bad save. AMD might of saved me money, but for the last 5 years Intel has kept me at the top of my game. going AMD could save you a bit of cash if thats a problem.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
